        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 29 at 7:26PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 725 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Huntsville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northern Huntsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
